<section id="legacy" class="py-16 bg-gray-50">
  <div class="container mx-auto px-4 max-w-4xl">
    <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-8">Legacy and Impact</h2>
    <div class="prose max-w-none">
      <p class="text-xl mb-6">
        Now in his fifties, Seth continues to innovate at the intersection of technology, art, and community. His career represents a remarkable thread through the evolution of digital culture – from the early days of interactive CD-ROMs to the blockchain-powered art galleries of today.
      </p>
      
      <p class="text-lg text-gray-600 mb-6">
        What distinguishes Seth's career is his consistent bridging of artistic and technological worlds. While many tech entrepreneurs focus solely on business metrics, and many artists remain distant from technological innovation, Seth has spent decades creating meaningful intersections between these domains. This has allowed him to identify opportunities that others miss and build platforms that resonate on deeper human levels.
      </p>

      <blockquote class="border-l-4 border-blue-500 pl-4 italic text-gray-700 my-8">
        "Money is not the goal, it's a means of helping you work on what you want, when you want and with whom you want."
      </blockquote>

      <blockquote class="border-l-4 border-blue-500 pl-4 italic text-gray-700 my-8">
        "I doubt that I will ever give up trying to create new things."
      </blockquote>

      <p class="text-lg text-gray-600 mb-6">
        Throughout his journey, Seth has mentored countless entrepreneurs and creators, sharing his experience through formal programs like the U.S. State Department's Global Entrepreneurship Program and informal relationships with emerging founders. His support for artists transitioning into new technological frontiers has been particularly significant, helping traditional creators navigate the complexities of blockchain, NFTs, and generative systems.
      </p>

      <blockquote class="border-l-4 border-blue-500 pl-4 italic text-gray-700 my-8">
        "We built a diverse team of people from Venice Beach to New York to Tokyo to Buenos Aires. To see folks in their twenties who came of age at a very difficult time during Covid develop valuable skills in smart contracts, web3 marketing, live event production, generative AI—that's really special. That's our real legacy."
      </blockquote>

      <p class="text-lg text-gray-600 mb-6">
        Seth Goldstein's career defies simple categorization – he is simultaneously entrepreneur, artist, investor, community builder, and futurist. What remains consistent is his ability to see emerging possibilities before others and his commitment to using technology to enhance human creativity and connection. From digitizing Robert Wilson's theatrical archives in 1992 to minting generative art in Venice in 2024, Seth has remained true to his vision of technology as a tool for expanding human expression and building meaningful communities.
      </p>

      <blockquote class="border-l-4 border-blue-500 pl-4 italic text-gray-700 my-8">
        "As much as we want to believe that the process of incubating startups can be reduced to science, the fact remains that it is an innately artistic, human process, and therefore filled with messy emotions, complex motivations, and latent triggers."
      </blockquote>

      <p class="text-lg text-gray-600">
        In a world increasingly dominated by algorithms and optimization, Seth Goldstein continues to champion the human, the creative, and the unexpected – always with one foot slightly over the ledge, pioneering new possibilities at the frontier of what's possible.
      </p>
